About this talk¶

Previous talk https://artofmaps.netlify.app/ showcasing map art using R and JavaScript

This talk is another showcase of map art, that looks like wall art

Opportunity to try out the following in 4 days:

  • Python map packages
  • Deploying concept to webapp using Python
  • Agentic AI

Note this is a personal project and in no way reflects any work or opinions on any of my employers

Southland, New Zealand¶

  • Map created with contextily Python package using the Place API

  • Uses the Macrostrat tile layer

    Macrostrat is a platform for the aggregation and distribution of geological data relevant to the spatial and temporal distribution of sedimentary, igneous, and metamorphic rocks as well as data extracted from them.

  • The colours are related to the lithology ie the physical characteristics of a rock, including colour, composition, and texture

Southland, New Zealand Walking Trails¶

  • Map created with OSMnx Python package

    OSMnx is a Python package to easily download, model, analyze, and visualize street networks and other geospatial features from OpenStreetMap.

  • OSMnx is built on Matplotlib and you can customise OSMnx plots using Matplotlib's API

Conclusion¶

The tools that made this presentation possible:

  • Jupyter notebooks for interactively developing Python
  • OSMnx is pronounced as the initialism: oh-ess-em-en-ex. It is built on top of NetworkX and GeoPandas, and interacts with OpenStreetMap APIs
  • contextily package to retrieve tile maps from the internet
  • nbconvert package to convert Notebooks to other formats
  • reveal.js & theme solarized to create slides with one palette
  • Netlify to deploy the presentation.slides.html to a custom URL

What I learnt

  • How to static maps that look like wall art
  • Matplotlib is a useful and compatible base mapping package
  • Rapid prototyping and plotting with matplotlib seemed straightforward
  • Customisation seems finicky with a steeper learning curve with matplotlib https://stackoverflow.com/questions/40796117/how-do-i-make-the-width-of-the-title-box-span-the-entire-plot
  • Agentic AI was great at scaffolding the initial project and telling me "You're right". In this project I preferred googling blogs and reading docs to learn these new Python packages

References¶

  • Boeing, G. (2025). Modeling and Analyzing Urban Networks and Amenities with OSMnx. Geographical Analysis, published online ahead of print. doi:10.1111/gean.70009

  • Interactive presentations from a Jupyter Notebook

  • x lines of Python: static basemaps with contextily
